<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf02adc2f-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s7997"><num value="7997">§ 7997.</num><heading> Tracking of benefits</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">As soon as practicable after <date date="2002-05-13">May 13, 2002</date>, the Secretary shall establish procedures to track the benefits provided, directly or indirectly, to individuals and entities under titles I and II and the amendments made by those titles.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf02adc30-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/171/tI/s1614">Pub. L. 107–171, title I, § 1614</ref>, <date date="2002-05-13">May 13, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/222">116 Stat. 222</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idf02adc31-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idf02adc32-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="idf02adc33-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Titles I and II, referred to in text, mean titles I and II of <ref href="/us/pl/107/171">Pub. L. 107–171</ref>, <date date="2002-05-13">May 13, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/143">116 Stat. 143</ref>. For complete classification of titles I and II of <ref href="/us/pl/107/171">Pub. L. 107–171</ref> to the Code, see Tables.</p>
</note>
</notes>
